spirit:enumeration.spirit:text: GTH: Serial RapidIO Gen2 3.125 Gb/s default (Pre-Production)

spirit:component.spirit:description: The UltraScale FPGAs Transceivers Wizard provides a simple and robust method of configuring one or more serial transceivers. Start from scratch, or use a configuration preset to target an industry standard. The highly flexible Transceivers Wizard generates a customized IP core for the transceivers, configuration options, and enabled ports you've selected, optionally including a variety of helper blocks to simplify common functionality. In addition, it can produce an example design for simple simulation and hardware usage demonstration.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: GT_TYPE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: For devices which contain more than one serial transceiver type, select the type of transceiver to configure

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: GT_REV
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the serial transceiver silicon revision

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: GT_DIRECTION
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enable transmit and/or receive

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_ENABLE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enable the receiver for use

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_ENABLE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enable the transmitter for use

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: CHANNEL_ENABLE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Indicate whether this transceiver channel is instantiated and enabled for use

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_MASTER_CHANNEL
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Designate an enabled transceiver as the master TX channel for various purposes such as user clock generation and buffer bypass (if selected)

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_MASTER_CHANNEL
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Designate an enabled transceiver as the master RX channel for various purposes such as user clock generation and buffer bypass (if selected)

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: LOCATE_COMMON
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: If a QPLL is used for either the transmitter or the receiver, indicate whether the transceiver COMMON block is instantiated within the core, or outside of the core in the example design. Exclusion from the core may allow placement of separate but compatible transceiver interfaces within a single quad.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_PPM_OFFSET
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: PPM offset between receiver and transmitter
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Specify the PPM offset between received data and transmitted data

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: OOB_ENABLE
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Enable Out of Band signaling (OOB)/Electrical Idle
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enable or disable Out of Band signaling (OOB)/Electrical Idle

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_SSC_PPM
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Specify the spread spectrum clocking modulation in PPM

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: INS_LOSS_NYQ
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Indicate the transmitter to receiver insertion loss at the Nyquist frequency, in dB

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_LINE_RATE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Enter the transmitter line rate in Gb/s

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_PLL_TYPE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the transmitter PLL type

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_REFCLK_FREQUENCY
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select a transmitter reference clock frequency from among those supported for the selected line rate and PLL type

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_DATA_ENCODING
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the encoding format for data transmission, or choose 'Raw' for no data encoding

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_USER_DATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the width at which the user logic will provide parallel data to the serial transceiver for transmission

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_INT_DATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the width of the serial transceiver internal transmitter data path

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_BUFFER_MODE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select whether to enable or to bypass the transmitter buffer

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_QPLL_FRACN_NUMERATOR

spirit:parameter.spirit:description: For applicable GTY transmitter line rates, enter the numerator which produces the desired 24-bit fractional part of the QPLL feedback divider as displayed. Note that changes affect transmitter reference clock options including current selection

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_OUTCLK_SOURCE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the source of TXOUTCLK

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TX_DIFF_SWING_EMPH_MODE

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_LINE_RATE

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_PLL_TYPE

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_REFCLK_FREQUENCY

spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the decoding format for data reception, or choose 'Raw' for no data decoding

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_USER_DATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the width at which the serial transceiver will provide received parallel data to the user logic

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_INT_DATA_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the width of the serial transceiver internal receiver data path

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_BUFFER_MODE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select whether to enable or to bypass the receiver elastic buffer

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_QPLL_FRACN_NUMERATOR
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Fractional part of QPLL feedback divider
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: For applicable GTY receiver line rates, enter the numerator which produces the desired 24-bit fractional part of the QPLL feedback divider as displayed. Note that changes affect receiver reference clock options including current selection. When receiver and transmitter share a QPLL, values must match and are set by the transmitter selection

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: LOCATE_RESET_CONTROLLER
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Indicate whether the transceiver reset controller is instantiated within the core, or outside of the core in the example design. Inclusion may simplify transceiver usage, while exclusion may allow greater control.

spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Include transmitter buffer bypass controller in the

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: LOCATE_RX_BUFFER_BYPASS_CONTROLLER
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Include receiver elastic buffer bypass controller in the
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: If the receiver elastic buffer is bypassed, indicate whether the receiver elastic buffer bypass controller is instantiated within the core, or outside of the core in the example design. Inclusion may simplify transceiver usage, while exclusion may allow greater control.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: LOCATE_TX_USER_CLOCKING
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Include simple transmitter user clocking network in the
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Indicate whether the simple, inferred transmitter user clocking network is instantiated within the core, or outside of the core in the example design. Inclusion may simplify transceiver usage, while exclusion allows greater control of the network.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: LOCATE_RX_USER_CLOCKING
